reviews.review_text:
Beter than the Soundboard This is a great show.  I think this AUD is alot beter than the SBD.

This show is famous for the "playin" but theres lots of other goodies here too.

Playin' in the Band!!!!!! This is a VERY exciting version of this song. The boys sound like they were transported back to 1974 at times, to 1977 at times, and so on.  The rest of the show pales in comparison, but is still ok.  Get it for the badass Playin'.

Unfortunately Track 5 from set 2 is 36+ minutes and stretches from the start of drums and then cuts on 3/4 through Corinna. How did that happen? Would be nice to have a properly tracked version of what is one of the best sets of 1993.

Jerry's Playin' whole step modulation licks! Wow! Check it out! Jerry modulates a whole step "up" in the melody 3 times in this PITB version!! He used to play the entire song like that early on. In the later years it became a treat to hear it every once in awhile when PLAYIN'was selected! NICE AUD.!

a great show all around, incedibly special set 2 1st set opener is fun and the HCS is beautiful as always. I could keep talking about the first set but I can't hold it back any longer...
SET 2 PLAYIN is potent psychedelic craziness and fun. wonderfully long and chaotic in the best way. despite the tracking error during drumz>space>corrina (i kept the extra music as  d2 filler or you can use the other AUD sources' drums>space>corrina>) i am of the opinion the this is a must have 93 show. no doubt about it.

Sick FOB Very punchy and crisp FOB recording. The taper had his techniques dialed...very little crowd noise with wide dynamic and freq. ranges. Micky and Billy are especially well represented. Nice Sampson opener and the Playin' is special.

too bad about the screwed up tracking.

WOW 93 Yaaa this is really good, im really enjoying Broken Arrow, Deal, and Crazy Fingers, Jerry is awesome and Phil has the crazy fingers in that one, just perfect and really trippy. Had some of this on a mysterious tape along time ago , thanks Archive, Recorders, and uploaders. I missed this.
